               <msContents>
                  <summary>Summary statement from the government bank at Theadelphia of receipts from poll-tax and "merismoi" during the first accounting period of the year; the names are in alphabetical order</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the back there is P.Col. V 1 verso 3</note>
                     <note type="general">The columns are not numbered</note>
                     <note type="general">This document was a summary statement of the bank; unlike in P.Col. 1 recto 2, names and payment were entered at the same time</note>
                     <note type="general">Double check lines are drawn next to a name when the amount was paid</note>
                     <note type="general">The use of the month name Hadrianos instead of Choiak indicates that the text was written after 130 AD</note>
                     <note type="general">The pig tax appears only when a man had died during the year</note>
                     <note type="general">10 cols. of writing by the same small and practiced hand throughout: 31 lines in col. 1; 31 in col. 2; 34 in col. 3; 34 in col. 5; 28 in col. 6; 27 in col. 7; 30 in col. 8; 29 in col 9; 27 in col. 10</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
